Colgate and UAlbany also played in the 2007 opener, a 13-11 victory for the Raiders ... the Great Danes have lost four of five overtime games playing in the program's history ... Herb Glass made a 48-yard field in the first quarter, tying the third longest in school history ... Glass became the school's all-time scoring leader as a placekicker with 174 points, moving past Bryan Bagstad (1999-2001) ... Dillon Romain's 75-yard TD reception tied the ninth-longest pass play in UAlbany history ...UAlbany is 4-9 in openers as a NCAA FCS program.  Hamilton, N.Y. - Nate Eachus scored on a one-yard run in overtime to lift Colgate to a 37-34 victory over UAlbany in the season opener for both teams on Saturday, Sept. 3 before 6,748 fans at Andy Kerr Stadium.      UAlbany grabbed a 34-31 lead in the extra period when Herb Glass booted a 41-yard field goal. The Raiders moved seven plays for the winning points. The key play came on third-and-10 at the 25-yard line.
